requestTemplates.body:
Dear Open Records Officer,

Pursuant to the Georgia Open Records Act, O.C.G.A. § 50-18-70 et seq., I respectfully request access to the following public records:

{record_description}

Specific Details:
• Date Range: {date_range_text}
• Location/Department: {location_text}
• Additional Details: {incident_details_text}

Please provide the records in {preferred_format} format. I understand that under O.C.G.A. § 50-18-71(b)(1), you have up to three (3) business days to respond to this request.

If you determine that any portion of the requested records is exempt from disclosure, please provide a written explanation citing the specific legal authority (Code section, subsection, and paragraph) exempting those records from disclosure, as required by O.C.G.A. § 50-18-71(d).

Regarding fees, I understand that the first 15 minutes of search and retrieval time is provided without charge, and copying fees shall not exceed $0.10 per page for standard copies. If the estimated cost will exceed $25.00, please notify me before beginning production as required by law.

If you have any questions about this request or need clarification, please contact me at {requester_phone} or {requester_email}.

Thank you for your prompt attention to this matter.

Sincerely,

{requester_name}
{requester_address}
Phone: {requester_phone}
Email: {requester_email}

Dear Open Records Officer,

Pursuant to the Georgia Open Records Act, O.C.G.A. § 50-18-70 et seq., I respectfully request access to the following public records:

{record_description}

Specific Details:
• Incident Date: {date_range_text}
• Location: {location_text}
• Case/Report Number (if known): {incident_details_text}
• Type of Incident: {incident_type}

I understand that under O.C.G.A. § 50-18-72(a)(3) and (4), records compiled for law enforcement purposes may be exempt if production would disclose confidential sources, investigative material, endanger safety, or concern pending investigations.

For any records that may be subject to these exemptions, please provide:
1. A description of the responsive records
2. The specific legal authority for withholding (Code section, subsection, and paragraph)
3. Any portions that can be released with appropriate redactions

Per O.C.G.A. § 50-18-77, I note that basic information from police incident reports (names of arrested persons, offenses, investigating officer, date/time/location, and brief incident description) should be available for public inspection.

Please respond within three (3) business days as required by law. If costs will exceed $25.00, please provide an estimate before proceeding.

Contact Information:
{requester_name}
{requester_address}
Phone: {requester_phone}
Email: {requester_email}

Thank you for your assistance.

Sincerely,
{requester_name}
